
[1]occasional

   OCCA'SIONAL, a. s as z.

   1. Incidental; casual; occurring at times, but not regular or
   systematic; made or happening as opportunity requires or admits. We
   make occasional remarks on the events of the age.

   2. Produced by accident; as the occasional origin of a thing.

   3. Produced or made on some special event; as an occasional discourse.
     __________________________________________________________________

